Give me a breakdown of all the Perazzi sponsored shooters.', 'Certainly. Perazzi’s approach to sponsorship is rooted in partnership and stewardship rather than simple endorsement. The brand supports a select group of elite shooters across disciplines—primarily through providing guns, custom configurations, and priority service. These athletes serve as both competitors and ambassadors, embodying the values of craft, performance, and long-term relationship that define Perazzi.

Below is a summary of notable Perazzi-sponsored and supported shooters, as reflected in official Perazzi USA and international references:

---

## **Olympic & International Trap and Skeet**

- **Ennio Mattarelli (Italy)**  
  1964 Olympic Trap Gold (Tokyo) with an early Perazzi prototype. Collaborated with Daniele Perazzi on the MX8’s development.

- **Luciano Giovannetti (Italy)**  
  Back-to-back Olympic Trap Gold medals (1980, 1984) with Perazzi.

- **Kim Rhode (USA)**  
  Six-time Olympic medalist; won her first gold at Atlanta 1996 in Double Trap with a Perazzi. Continued to win medals in Skeet/Trap using customized Perazzi guns (MX12/MX8). Famous for her long-term attachment to a single Perazzi gun, which was stolen and later recovered. (No longer shoots a Perazzi.)

- **Michael Diamond (Australia)**  
  Two-time Olympic Trap Gold medalist (1996, 2000), multiple world titles with MX-series guns.

- **David Kostelecky (Czech Republic)**  
  2008 Olympic Trap Gold; long-term Perazzi partner.

- **Giovanni Pellielo (Italy)**  
  Four Olympic medals (2000–2016) using Perazzi MX8 derivatives.

- **Jessica Rossi (Italy)**  
  2012 Olympic Trap Gold with a world-record score; used Perazzi. Italy’s London 2012 shotgun team, armed with Perazzis, contributed to 12 of 15 Olympic shotgun medals that year.

- **Diana Bacosi & Gabriele Rossetti (Italy)**  
  2016 Olympic Skeet Gold medalists (women’s and men’s) using Perazzi (Rossetti with MX2000S).

---

## **Sporting Clays & FITASC**

- **George Digweed (UK)**  
  Over 25 world titles in Sporting Clays and FITASC. Won many major titles with Perazzi MX2000 and MX8 models.

- **David Radulovich (USA)**  
  Multiple World Cup and World Champion in FITASC. Won many major titles with Perazzi High Tech S. Top-level sporting clays champion and respected coach.

- **Wendell Cherry (USA)**  
  Multiple National and US Open titles with Perazzi MX2000. Key figure in modern Perazzi brand storytelling.

- **Tamás Jeri (Hungary)**  
  World title holder; uses a Perazzi High Tech Sporting, crafted to his measurements. Credits the Perazzi’s stability and smooth swing as key factors in his championship run.

---

## **American Trap & Skeet**

