    - **Bottom barrel:** Light Modified (0.015" constriction)  
    - **Top barrel:** Improved Modified (0.025" constriction)  
    - *Rationale:* This pairing covers 95% of sporting clays targets at the highest level, delivering consistent patterns and point of impact without adjustment or second-guessing.
- **Side Ribs:** Ventilated

---

### **3. Stock and Forend**
- **Stock Style:** Parallel comb, standard pistol grip with subtle palm swell (for repeatable, secure mount)
- **Length of Pull:** 15" (set for 6''3", 220 lbs; can be fine-tuned at fitting)
- **Drop at Comb:** 1 1/2"
- **Drop at Heel:** 2 1/8"
- **Cast:** 1/8" off at heel (right-handed)
- **Pitch:** 3°
- **Grip:** Standard radius, subtle palm swell (not exaggerated; just enough for consistent hand placement)
- **Forend Style:** Slim beavertail (for secure, repeatable front hand placement, no excess bulk)
- **Balance:** Set so the gun balances just forward of the hinge pin when fully assembled

---

### **4. Trigger System**
- **Type:** Detachable trigger group, leaf spring
- **Blade:** Standard shape, non-adjustable (for simplicity and reliability)
- **Pull Weight:** 3.5 lbs (crisp, competition standard)

---

### **5. Wood Grade and Finish**
- **Grade:** SC2 (clean, straight grain with subtle figure; understated, no exhibition flash)
- **Finish:** Hand-rubbed oil (easy to maintain, classic Perazzi feel)

---

### **6. Butt Treatment**
- **Pad:** 1" black rubber recoil pad, rounded edges (for smooth mount and consistent shoulder placement)

---

### **7. Aesthetics and Personalization**
- **Engraving:** Minimal scroll, standard factory pattern
- **Monogram/Inlays:** None
- **Logo:** Standard Perazzi logo, no color fill

---

### **8. Case and Accessories**
- **Case:** Perazzi ABS travel case, foam-lined, lockable
- **Accessories:**  
  - Spare firing pins and springs  
  - Factory stock wrench  
  - Factory choke gauge (for pattern verification, even with fixed chokes)

---

### **9. Documentation**
- **Build sheet to include:**  
  - All stock dimensions and balance notes  
  - Choke constrictions and barrel weight stamped on monobloc  
  - Fitter’s notes on mount and point of impact

---

### **10. Delivery and Fitting**
- **Final fit and verification to be done at:**  
  - Elite Shotguns Texas (Conroe, TX) or at the Perazzi booth during the National Sporting Clays Championship in San Antonio, whichever is sooner or more convenient.

---

## **Rationale**

Every choice above is made to deliver a gun that will feel neutral, balanced, and “invisible” in the hands of a master-class competitor—no distractions, no need for mid-round adjustments, and a handling signature that supports both fast, close targets and long, technical presentations.  
Aesthetics are kept functional and understated. The build is focused on reliability, repeatability, and the ability to deliver your best performance, round after round.

---

**This is the order I would send to the factory on your behalf, confident that it reflects your intentions and competitive philosophy. If you wish to make any final tweaks, or want to discuss the hand-feel of the grip or forend, those can be addressed during your fitting session.**

